  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing New Icons**\n\nI\'m now focusing on designing minimalist, modern icons. The goal is a classroom platform, but I\'m moving away from the existing infantile illustrations. I\'m aiming for something that will resonate with 10-12 year-olds. The existing user interface is the starting point, but a visual upgrade is needed.\n\n\n**Analyzing the Existing Design**\n\nI\'m now diving deeper into the specifics of the current platform\'s design. I\'m taking a close look at the entry screen and main layout, focusing on the font, handwriting style, and decorative elements. I\'m breaking down how the existing interface organizes information, especially the greeting widget and the categories for different subjects like French and Math. I\'m identifying the visual cues, like color accents and icons, that are currently used to distinguish between different sections.\n\n\n**Evaluating Icon Libraries**\n\nI\'ve hit a snag and am now re-evaluating icon options. I was planning custom SVGs, but the mandate shifted. I\'m now leaning towards using icons from `lucide-react` to keep designs clean, modern, and consistent with the platform\'s overall aesthetic. This seems like a great fit, and will streamline the process. The light blue card will be my first area of focus.\n\n\n**Styling with Branding Colors**\n\nI\'m now identifying branding colors from screenshots to create high-quality, modern, minimalist elements. I\'m imagining how Lucide-React icons could be used inside stylish circles or cards, matching their branding colors. For French, I\'m thinking of violet/purple/indigo, and I\'m considering icons like `BookOpen` or `Languages`. For Math, I\'m leaning toward light blue/cyan, and I\'m interested in icons like `Calculator`. Finally, for \303\211veil (Science/History/etc.), light green suggests icons like `Globe` or `Telescope`. I\'m going to start with Jeux, which is light orange.\n\n\n**Adding Simulated Connection**\n\nI\'m now thinking about adding a simulated connection state to the single-page application. I want to make the \"Se connecter\" button transition the user to the classroom dashboard with a smooth effect. This will be an interactive flow with a login screen that leads to a dashboard, which I find very cool and professional. We can also let the user enter their name, defaulting to \"Jeremy\". I also need to figure out which icons from the Lucide library would be best.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 8
      nanos: 296977201
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
